modules.description: This module maps file extensions to MIME types and vice versa using filename patterns or MIME type strings. It provides `lookup` to get a MIME type from a filename, using a default if specified, and `reverse_lookup` to retrieve possible file extensions for a given MIME type. It is useful for determining content types in web servers or file-handling applications where accurate MIME type detection is needed.

This module maps file extensions and filenames to MIME types based on RFC2045 standards, using internal data to perform lookups. It supports converting extensions to MIME types, filenames to MIME types by extracting their extension, and MIME types back to lists of associated extensions. Use cases include determining the correct MIME type for serving files over HTTP or validating file types based on extension or MIME type.
